{
  "bio": [
    "Steve Ells helped pioneer fast-casual dining as the founder of Chipotle.",
    "After studying at the Culinary Institute of America, Ells opened the first Chipotle in Denver, Colorado in 1993.",
    "He hoped to use the profits to fund a fine dining restaurant, but Chipotle was so successful he ended up expanding to a second store in 1995 and a third in 1996.",
    "Today, Chipotle sells $11.3 billion worth of burritos, bowls and salads each year across 3,700 stores around the world.",
    "Ells stepped down as CEO in 2018 and as executive chairman in 2020.",
    "He opened a new restaurant concept, a robot-manned \"restaurant of the future\" named Kernel, in New York City in 2024."
  ],
  "about": [
    "Ells sold big chunks of Chipotle to McDonald's beginning in 1998 to help the brand expand. By the time Chipotle went public in 2006, he owned less than 4%."
  ]
}